					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/d-l-k-fernworth" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(466570); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=466570&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610246704" alt="D-L-K-Fernworth" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=466570)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/d-l-k-fernworth" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(466570); return false;" >D-L-K-Fernworth</a></span> <span class="odate time_1271226334 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">14 Apr 2010 06:25</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-752737">
									

<p>So then, this proposal claims that SCP-001 is just reporting on SCP's, not creating them, unless it knew it would be opened at least 129 times and could therefore create the disease in advance.</p>
<p>I don't think it's a problem, it just makes this SCP-001 proposal all more worrysome.</p>

