				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/doctor-ge-smith" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1786409); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1786409&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610246704" alt="Doctor GE Smith" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1786409)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/doctor-ge-smith" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1786409); return false;" >Doctor GE Smith</a></span> <span class="odate time_1386507084 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">08 Dec 2013 12:51</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1910962">
									

<p>Alternately, this could be a return to the theme of retroactive alterations to reality. Perhaps colds used to have a mundane cause, or perhaps prior to these changes, humanity had never been plagued with low-level sinus and respiratory ailments&#8230;Dun dun DUUUUUHHHNNN!!!<br />
Not the strongest dread I've felt reading SCP, but an interesting thought. Were that to be the case, it would beg an odd question: why wouldn't humanity have weak ailments?<br />
bad for not reading more comments before making my own. I did not mean to steal MyBuddyBill's dramatic sting!</p>

